  "body": "# User can send messages to blocked contact\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\nUsers are able to send messages to contacts they have blocked. We want when a contact has been blocked by the user, they should not be able to send the blocked contact a message. If the user unblocks the contact, they should be able to send messages to the contact again.\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nSending message to a blocked contact is disabled\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nSending message to a blocked contact is allowed\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1) Open Status\r\n2) Block a contact from your contacts lists\r\n3) Try send a message to the blocked contact\r\n4) Confirm that you were able to send a message to the blocked contact\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly \r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please, add logs/notes if necessary)\r\n\r\n",
